properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 7:01PM CST until January 4 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Quick Round of Snow Through Tonight...

.Light to moderate snow will continue across parts of eastern
Iowa through the late evening. Narrow bands of heavier snow will
drop visibilities below a half mile for a brief time and quickly
lead to slushy accumulation on untreated pavement. Total snow
accumulations are expected to range from 1 to 3 inches.

* WHAT...Snow with some breaks, especially from Vinton to
Williamsburg and Iowa City. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 2
inches with isolated amounts near 3 inches possible. Brief
moderate to heavy snow bands may drop visibilities below a half
mile. Expect slushy accumulations on untreated roads.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and northeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and quick drops in
visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST SATURDAY
